  "prompt": "Can I graduate college with 1.8 GPA?",
  "response": "Graduating with a 1.8 GPA can be challenging, as most colleges have minimum GPA requirements for graduation. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Typical minimum GPA requirements:\n- Most colleges require a minimum 2.0 GPA to graduate\n- Some specific programs may require higher GPAs\n\n2. Potential options:\n- Speak with academic advisors about your specific situation\n- Look into academic probation or improvement plans\n- Consider taking additional courses to raise your GPA\n- Evaluate credit recovery or grade forgiveness options\n\n3. Potential consequences of a low GPA:\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Limited graduate school opportunities\n- Challenges with professional certifications\n\n4. Proactive steps:\n- Meet with academic advisors\n- Develop a study strategy\n- Seek tutoring\n- Focus on improving academic performance\n\nThe exact requirements vary by institution, so it's best to:\n- Check your specific college's graduation requirements\n- Consult with academic advisors\n- Create a plan to improve your academic standing\n\nEvery situation is unique, so personalized guidance from your college's academic support services is recommended.",
